<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<theorem xmlns="Theorem"
         xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
         type="Proposition"
         id="Thm_DoubleInverse"
         xsi:schemaLocation="Theorem file:/C:/xampp/htdocs/moodle/mod/msm/NewSchemas/Theorem.xsd">
   <caption>Double inverse of a linear map</caption>
   <statement.theorem>
      <para>
         <para.body>If the linear transformation <math>
               <latex>L\from \RNr[n]\to \RNr[n]</latex>
            </math> is invertible, with inverse <math>
               <latex>M=L^{-1}</latex>
            </math>, then <math>
               <latex>M</latex>
            </math> is also invertible and</para.body>
      </para>
      <math.display>
         <latex>L = M^{-1} = \left( L^{-1} \right)^{-1}</latex>
      </math.display>
   </statement.theorem>
   <proof>
      <proof.block>
         <proof.block.body>
            <para>
               <para.body>By definition of <math>
                     <latex>L^{-1}</latex>
                  </math>, we write <math>
                     <latex>M=L^{-1}</latex>
                  </math> because there is a linear transformation <math>
                     <latex>M</latex>
                  </math> with</para.body>
            </para>
            <math.display>
               <latex>M\Comp L = \Id[n] = L\Comp M</latex>
            </math.display>
            <para>
               <para.body>These two equations, however, also mean that <math>
                     <latex>M</latex>
                  </math> is invertible and that <math>
                     <latex>M^{-1} = L</latex>
                  </math>. But then</para.body>
            </para>
            <math.array column="3">
               <row rowspan="1">
                  <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
                     <math>
                        <latex>L</latex>
                     </math>
                  </cell>
                  <cell colspan="1" halign="center" valign="middle">
                     <text>=	</text>
                     <companion>
                        <info>
                           <para>
                              <para.body>... as we just said</para.body>
                           </para>
                        </info>
                     </companion>
                  </cell>
                  <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
                     <math>
                        <latex>M^{-1}</latex>
                     </math>
                  </cell>
               </row>
               <row rowspan="1">
                  <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle"/>
                  <cell colspan="1" halign="center" valign="middle">
                     <text>=	</text>
                     <companion>
                        <info>
                           <para>
                              <para.body>substitute <math>
                                    <latex>L^{-1}</latex>
                                 </math> for <math>
                                    <latex>M</latex>
                                 </math>
                              </para.body>
                           </para>
                        </info>
                     </companion>
                  </cell>
                  <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
                     <math>
                        <latex>\left( L^{-1} \right)^{-1}</latex>
                     </math>
                  </cell>
               </row>
            </math.array>
            <para>
               <para.body>This was to be shown.</para.body>
            </para>
         </proof.block.body>
      </proof.block>
   </proof>
</theorem>
